AIR France-KLM has reassured customers of its commitment to better flight services in Nigeria. The group also said it would further strengthen the partnerships between Nigeria and their home countries. Addressing journalists in Lagos, the Executive Vice President, Commercial Division, Air France KLM, Pieter Bootsma, said in the past 75 years, the airline had been connecting customers to the world with direct flights between Lagos with Nigeria being a very important market. Bootsma said that Africa and indeed Nigeria had always been a cornerstone in the network of KLM, adding that customers from Africa were all over the world and to have Africa in their network is very important. According to him, Africa is a very important part of the network and Air France KLM group is the main player between Europe and Africa. The Country Manager, Air France- KLM Nigeria, Christine Quantin, said the aim of the company was to move customerâ€™s world by creating memorable experiences. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com